This paper is about natural language processing and machine learning, which suggests that it likely belongs to the Computer Science sub-category of "cs.CL" (Computation and Language). The paper specifically focuses on the use of BERT, a popular language model, which suggests that it may also belong to "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) and "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of transfer learning and fine-tuning, which are common techniques in neural networks, suggesting that it may also belong to "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses a story ending prediction task, which involves understanding and analyzing visual information, suggesting that it may also belong to "cs.CV" (Computer Vision).
